|YKODarkwind offers many ways to customize your character, including
races, guilds, alignment, equipment, and many others. This document
serves to document those items.

|WKB--<< STANDARD RACES >>--

|YKOThe following races are available at the Darkwind Hall of Races:

|CKBDarkwinder- |WKOThe humans that live around Darkwind City are collectively
known as Darkwinders. Darkwinders are about average among the civilized races 
in terms of physical and mental powers, but are well accepted by most other 
cultures due to the importance of the city in world affairs.|WKB
    - |GKBThis race can join any guild.|WKB
    - |YKB+EXP  +RACE CHANGE|000

|BCBBarbarian- |WKOThe Barbarians are an offshoot of modern human society that
settled south of Darkwind City in a settlement known as Canith. Their rugged 
lifestyle tends towards the development of stronger, healthier bodies than 
most humans. Canith society values order, and pursuit of the common good. 
Barbarians are generally friendly to strangers and always eager to learn about 
exotic people and places.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBNECRO, PRIEST, SWASH|WKB
    - |YKB+CHR +CON +STR +EXP  +GOOD|000

|CK0Glavian- |WKOGlavians are humans that hail from the mountain kingdom of
Glavia. Glavians are a generally good-aligned people used to opposing 
demonic forces. Their society is otherwise peaceful and pastoral. Glavians 
are an inoffensive, likeable lot, with an open mind to new experiences.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBNECRO, PRIEST|WKB
    - |YKB+CHR +EXP +GOOD|000

|MCBFaerie- |WKOFaeries are a race of woodland sprites, usually diminutive in
stature. This group encompasses brownies, dryads, atomies, sylphs and
pixies, as well as sprites themselves.  They are known to be
extremely agile as well as friendly and typically good-looking, but
due to their generally small size they are not very strong or sturdy.  
They have a reputation, deserved or not, for being pranksters, and 
tend to be a bit flighty at times.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBFIGHTER|WKB
    - |YKB+WIS +PSION +WINGS +FLIGHT -SIZE|000

|GYBHalfling- |WKOHalflings are a race of short people much given to
the simpler pleasures in life, including good food, a warm bed, a 
window overlooking a pleasant little garden, a shady tree to lie 
under in the afternoon, and a full pipe after dinner.  They do not 
often become adventurers, but those that do are quite good at it.  
They are not too strong, because of their small size, and their 
homebody nature means they tend to be not as wary.  But halflings 
have truly incredible reflexes and are remarkably nimble and quick 
with their hands.  Halflings are most interested in having fun in life, 
and they take this attitude with them wherever they go.|WKB
    - |GKBThis race can join any guild.|WKB
    - |YKB+CHR +DEX -STR -WIS +DRINK +EAT -SIZE|000

|GKBHigh elf- |WKOThe elven kingdom south of Darkwind City is the home of the
High Elves. High Elf culture as a whole tends towards goodness in the context
of harmony with nature. High Elves have keen senses and are generally
superior mentally to most civilized races. Physically however, they can
be somewhat fragile and lack the robustness of other races.|000
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBNECRO, PRIEST|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT +WIS +CHR -CON +DAM_LIGHT +VISION|000

|YBBKender- |WKOThe Kender have always been hidden somewhere around the realms of
Darkwind. They are small jovial creatures with a love of adventure
and no fear. They are extremely agile, but are not known for a 
high level of common sense.|WKB
    - |GKBThis race can join any guild.|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +DEX -WIS +PSION -DAM_EVIL +VISION -SIZE|000

|MK0Rift duergar- |WKOThe Rift Duergar are a race of evil subterranean dwarves 
who have been twisted by dark forces into hateful caricatures of surface dwarves
They are short, stout and have hardy constitutions, enabling them to hold their
liquor and resist small amounts of magic and mental influence. Despite
being quite strong, Rift Duergar have problems balancing larger weapons
due to their stature.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join:
          |RKBBARD, CLERIC, GAROU, LUNAR, MAGE, NINJA, PALADIN, SWASH|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +CON -INT -CHR +MAGIC +PSION -DAM_LIGHT +EVIL +VISION
      +DRINK -SIZE|000

|MKBShel-zaranite- |WKOThe Shel-zaranites are an ancient offshoot of the elves 
that live deep underground. In their secluded city, they worship forgotten gods 
of evil. Dark Elves are quite agile and mentally superior to most
races, but are often sickly and lack constitution. Being an underground
race however, they are well adapted to lightless conditions.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBCLERIC, GAROU, LUNAR, MAGE, PALADIN|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT +WIS -CON -DAM_LIGHT +EVIL +VISION|000

|WWBSilver Elf- |WKOThe elven kingdom located on the highway between Darwind 
City and the frozen tundra is the home of the Silver Elves. Silver elves are 
also known as Moon Elves. Silver elf culture tends towards goodness and
as to please Luna, the moon Godess. Silver Elves have keen night vision, exude 
charisma, and are typically more intelligent, though less wise, than other races. 
Pyshically they are more nimble than what is typical, though they are rather 
fragile of constitution.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBFIGHTER, NECRO|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT +CHR -WIS -CON +GOOD +VISION|000

|BKBStone dwarf- |WKOStone Dwarves are a society of surface dwarves who long 
ago dedicated their lives to working in the underworld in the service of Mitra. 
Like most dwarves, they are short and stout and can hold their liquor, but 
Stone Dwarves also have a high degree of goodness ingrained into them at an 
early age. Their small size makes it difficult for them to wield larger 
weapons, and working in cramped mines have a detrimental effect on their joints,
limiting their agility.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBGAROU, NECRO, NINJA, PSION, PRIEST, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +CON -DEX +PSION +GOOD +VISION +DRINK -SIZE|000

|RKBUruk- |WKOThe Uruk are a loose tribe of marauding orcs which live in the 
Darkwind area, looting and pillaging small settlements. The Uruk value strength
and stamina over useless thought or a pretty face. They are a warlike race
that trains for battle from birth to death, acquiring a degree of proficiency
in the use of all weapons. They are particularly adapted to living in
marginal areas like shallow caves, or fetid swamps.|WKB
    - |YKO This race cannot join:
          |RKBBARD, CLERIC, GAROU, LUNAR, MAGE, NECRO, NINJA, PALADIN,
          PSION, SWASH|WKB
    - |YKO This race CAN join:
          |GKBDRAGON, FIGHTER, MORPHER, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +CON -INT -WIS -CHR +DAM_DISEASE +DAM_POISON +EVIL +VISION
      +WEAPON SPEC|000

The following races are available at the Hyperborea Hall of Races:

|WKOArctic elf- |WKOThe Arctic Elves are a subrace of the elves that have 
adapted to living in the far north of Hyperborea. Like all elves, they are 
bright and agile, but suffer from fragile bodies. Arctic elves are often at 
odds with the humans of northern Hyperborea, constantly fighting over territory 
and ancient artifacts of power in order to expand their evil society.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join: |RKBCLERIC, LUNAR, MAGE, PALADIN|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT +WIS -CON -DAM_FIRE +EVIL|000

|BK0Hyperborean gnome- |WKOHyperborean gnomes are a race of small humanoids 
that inhabit the more habitable rural areas of Hyperborea. They are bright and 
nimble, with a natural resistance to variations in the environment. They have a 
slight tendency to work towards the causes of good, if only because they are
subject to attack by the forces of evil. Like all gnomes, they are quite
small compared to other races, and have difficulty managing larger weapons.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join: |RKBFIGHTER, NECRO, PRIEST|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT +WIS +DAM_FIRE +DAM_ACID +DAM_POISON +GOOD +DRINK -SIZE|000

|RWOIce gnoll- |WKOIce Gnolls are an evil warrior race that appears to be a 
cross of some humanoid and a hyena. They are physically powerful but are 
lacking somewhat in intellect. Ice gnolls live to kill and eat; who their 
victims are is largely irrelevant.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:
          |RKBBARD, CLERIC, LUNAR, MAGE, PALADIN, PSION, SWASH, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +CON +DEX -INT -CHR +EVIL +EAT|000

|RWBIce ogre- |WKOIce Ogres are large brutish humanoids that live in the 
cold wastes of Hyperborea. Large numbers of them are regularly hired as 
mercenaries by the giants to wage war against more civilized races. They 
are immensely strong and rugged, but dimwitted and clumsy as well. They 
have no real culture to speak of except a penchant for violence. While not 
quite giant sized, ice ogres are large enough that they can wield large 
weapons much more easily than most other races.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:
          |RKBBARD, CLERIC, LUNAR, MAGE, NECRO, NINJA, PALADIN, PSION
          SWASH, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +CON -DEX -INT -WIS -CHR +DAM_DISEASE -DAM_PSION +EVIL
      +EAT +DRINK +SIZE|000

|WKBNorthman- |WKONorthmen are humans who settled in the frigid north. 
Northmen are widespread throughout Hyperborea, although most live in 
the city of Grimsfjord. Northmen are expert traders and hagglers, due 
to the need to trade with the southern cities for various goods not
produced in Hyperborea.|WKB
    - |GKBThis race can join any guild.|WKB
    - |YKB+CHR +EXP|000

|YKOThe following races are available at the Souvrael Hall of Races:

|YKODesert nomad- |WKOThe Desert Nomads are the wanderers of Souvrael. They 
are a deeply religious people who follow the teachings of their prophet. 
The are quick learners who have adapted to living in the open desert. Desert 
Nomads are known for their great hospitality, despite the harshness of 
their habitat.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join: |RKBNECRO, PRIEST|WKB
    - |YKB+CHR +CON +EXP +DAM_FIRE -DAM_WATER +GOOD|000

|YBBDesert dwarf- |WKOThe Desert Dwarves live in a small settlement in 
the deserts of Souvrael. The Dwarves live in a peaceful society, generally 
unaffected by outside influences. Physically, they are a short, hardy race. 
In addition to an innate resistance to magic and psionics, they tend to be 
quite healthy and strong, but suffer somewhat from a stubbiness in their 
limbs. Despite their strength, their small size often also creates difficulties
in wielding larger weapons.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join: |RKBGAROU, NECRO, NINJA, PRIEST, SWASH, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+STR +CON +WIS -DEX  +MAGIC +PSION +GOOD +DRINK +VISION -SIZE

|YKBSouvraeli- |WKOSouvraelis are the native humans of Souvrael who choose 
to live in cities instead of leading a nomadic existence. Their culture has 
evolved over time towards a more cosmopolitan lifestyle based on trade and 
education. As such, they are cunning negotiators, and have a thirst for 
knowledge.|WKB
    - |GKBThis race can join any guild.|WKB
    - |YKB+INT +CHR +EXP -DAM_WATER|000

|YKOThe following races are available at the Talamh Darag Hall of Races:

|GW0Crannian gnome- |WKOA race of small, misshapen, dwarf-like creatures that
dwell in the earth. The name 'gnome' was given to them by the medieval scholar 
Paracelcus, in an attempt to describe the most important of the earth spirits. 
Gnomes live under the earth, where they guard treasures. According to Paracelcus,
they move as easily through the earth as humans walk upon the ground.
They cannot stand the light of the sun, for even one ray would turn them
to stone. Some sources claim they spend the hours during daylight as a
toad. They are in some way related to goblins and dwarfs.
They have been known to steal neglected human babies to raise as their own.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join: |RKBGAROU, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT +CHR -CON +EXP +VISION -DRINK -EAT -SIZE|000

|MBBPixie- |WKOThe pixies are a race of small mischievous little fae. These 
smart little critters excel at finding ways to scare and trick their unsuspecting 
victims. They have beautiful silk-like wings that enable them to explore the 
skies and are naturally protected from the magical abilities of those who would 
hunt them. This sadistic little fae folk cares little about goodness.
    - |YKO This race cannot join: |RKBCLERIC, GAROU, FIGHTER, MAGE, LUNAR, PALADIN|WKB
    - |YKB+INT +MAGIC +EVIL +WINGS +FLIGHT -SIZE|000

|RB0Sidhe- |WKOThe Sidhe are a race of vile demonic creatures originating from 
the influential fae population of Talamh Darag. These Sidhe were infected
by a vampiric condition affecting their society on a large level.
The now unseelie Sidhe are known for their evil acts, magical abilities
and the moth-like wings that enable them to ascend from the ground.
The magical nature of the Sidhe fae allows them to regenerate their
abilities with greater ease then any other race would be able to.
Their weak body is able to purge toxics from their bloodstream at an 
increased rate, but suffers greatly where raw physical power is concerned.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:
          |RKBCLERIC, FIGHTER, GAROU, LUNAR, MAGE, PALADIN|WKB
    - |YKB+DEX +INT -CON -STR +EVIL +WINGS +FLIGHT +DRINK +SPREGEN -SIZE|000

|YCBWayfarian- |WKOThe wayfarians are a race of elves that have been oppressed 
by forces of evil for as long as they have been around. A powerful Paladin heroine
'Enelya Ar-Feiniel' who is now revered as their patron of adventurers sought
out Mitra's blessing to empower and protect her proud folk. This blessing
resulted in a holy and virtuous aura surrounding each member of the Wayfarian
race. This aura formed a defense against the evil acts of their foes and 
enabled them to strike out with a holy fury. Finally the Wayfarians were able 
to beat off their oppressors and build a new city. Their combined auras
helped form a powerful holy dome to protect this city against those who 
would seek to destroy it.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join: |RKBGAROU, NECRO, PRIEST, THIEF|WKB
    - |YKB+DAM_EVIL +DAM_CHAOS +GOOD +DAM TYPE GOOD|000


|WKB--<< EXOTIC RACES >>--

|CBBGypsy- |WKOThe Gypsy people are a skilled, artful traveling people.  They 
are very smart, charismatic and light fingered.  Singing, dancing, telling 
stories, fortune telling and lifting money from the rubes are the everyday 
events in the life of the Gyspy.  They prefer to wear bright colors, and usually 
speak freely, looking to make the next big score.
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:|RKBCLERIC, FIGHTER, NECRO|000

|RKBScro- |WKOThe Scro are an advanced form of orc that is well adapted to 
the rigors of travelling in wildspace. While they are not quite as strong 
nor robust as their more primitive cousins, they make up for this by possessing 
greater mental faculties and resistances to forces encountered in their more
exotic travels.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:|RKBBARD, CLERIC, MAGE, PALADIN|000

|CKBSylph- |WKOThe sky, mountains, and high places such as the tops of very 
tall trees are the favorite home of the Sylphs. Members of the Faerie race,
Sylph are roughly human in appearance with the exception of the almost
transparent wings on their backs. The Sylph are a culture that tends
towards goodness and lawfulness, but also one known for being able to
hold their own when it comes to the hearty consumption of the strong
libations served at the various festivals they hold. The Sylph are an
attractive race with looks to match their mental powers and quickness,
though they tend to be weaker and less robust than other races.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:|RKBNINJA, SWASH, NECRO|000

|MGBThraxian- |WKOThraxian draconians hail from the village of Thrax in 
eastern Hyperborea. While roughly humanoid in shape, they bear a striking 
similarity to their dragon cousins, including vestigial wings and a fiery 
breath weapon. They maintain some of the dragons' raw physical power and 
intellect as well. Their alien natures are not well received by other races, 
and their clawed hands are not well adapted to using most tools.|WKB
    - |YKOThis race cannot join:|RKBBARD, CLERIC, SWASH, THIEF|000

|YKOExotic races are those races found in areas throughout the game. Exotic
races are only available for players of level 45 and above. Racial attributes
for exotic races are available in their respective race room.

|YKOEach race has a unique set of abilities and penalties due to their physical
and mental characteristics, as well as cultural aspects of their societies,
some of which will be explained in more detail:

|CKBSTATS
|WKO-----
|YKORacial modifications to stats are made to the base stat, before other
modifications such as from magical equipment. Racial modifications are also
based on a percentage of the base stat. Thus even with an extremely strong
race, if you never raise your strength, your strength will be only one.
Because stats are always whole numbers, sometimes when you advance a stat
you have a penalty in, you may not see the effect of that stat raise.
Conversely, if you raise a stat you have a bonus in, you may see a rise of
two points instead of one.

|CKBALIGNMENT
|WKO---------
|YKOAdventurers are made, not born. By the time they choose the adventuring life,
adventurers have a lot of silly notions ingrained into their minds, especially
opinions about the role of alignment in society. Having been indoctrinated
from an early age, they will always have a tendency towards the predominant
attitudes of their culture. If you have a tendency towards one alignment,
you will be less affected by changes away from that alignment. You will also
be more affected by changes towards it.

